{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01W6o3S3BFCbGFrmLjSe4TbB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the full contents of the challenge-adapters file:\n\n## File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/challenge-adapters.ts`\n\nThe file contains the following key types and patterns:\n\n**Types:**\n- `GameSettledPlayer` — individual player from a settled game (userId, wallet, amountLamports, isWinner, payoutLamports, isCreator)\n- `GameSettledPayload` — the game.settled event payload (roundId, roundPda, game type, players array, feeLamports, settledAt)\n- `ChallengeAssignment` — a challenge with its definition (id, challengeId, action, scope, condition, target, progress, status)\n- `AdapterResult` — result from verification (shouldProgress boolean, progressDelta number)\n- `VerificationAdapter` — function type that takes (event, player, assignment) and returns AdapterResult\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `questEligible(player)` — gates whether a game counts toward challenges (returns false if isWinner === null for refunded games)\n- `gameCompletedAdapter` — checks if player participated and game matches scope\n- `gameWonAdapter` — checks if player won (isWinner === true) and game matches scope\n- `lobbyFilledAdapter` — checks if player is creator (isCreator === true) and game matches scope\n- `getAdapter(action)` — registry lookup that returns the adapter function or a no-op for unknown actions\n\n**Pattern:**\n1. Pure functions with no side effects\n2. Helper constants: `NO_PROGRESS` and `ONE_PROGRESS` for consistent returns\n3. Helper function `matchesScope()` for scope filtering logic\n4. All adapters follow the same signature and return structure\n5. Registry as a Map, with `getAdapter()` as the public lookup interface\n6. Each adapter checks scope first (returns NO_PROGRESS if scope doesn't match), then checks specific conditions\n\nThis is clean and extensible—new adapters just need to follow the `VerificationAdapter` type and be added to the registry."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"704bd991-5045-4113-8fa3-9bd3dc1e7fdb","uuid":"c9d2802a-e133-4c57-87f4-c5578860d7e6","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:38:07.061Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the file `backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/challenge-adapters.ts` and report its full contents. I need to see the types (GameSettledPayload, GameSettledPlayer, etc.) and the pattern used there, since I'll be creating a sibling handler file in the same directory.","agentId":"ad30402f8c11857de","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the full contents of the challenge-adapters file:\n\n## File: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/challenge-adapters.ts`\n\nThe file contains the following key types and patterns:\n\n**Types:**\n- `GameSettledPlayer` — individual player from a settled game (userId, wallet, amountLamports, isWinner, payoutLamports, isCreator)\n- `GameSettledPayload` — the game.settled event payload (roundId, roundPda, game type, players array, feeLamports, settledAt)\n- `ChallengeAssignment` — a challenge with its definition (id, challengeId, action, scope, condition, target, progress, status)\n- `AdapterResult` — result from verification (shouldProgress boolean, progressDelta number)\n- `VerificationAdapter` — function type that takes (event, player, assignment) and returns AdapterResult\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `questEligible(player)` — gates whether a game counts toward challenges (returns false if isWinner === null for refunded games)\n- `gameCompletedAdapter` — checks if player participated and game matches scope\n- `gameWonAdapter` — checks if player won (isWinner === true) and game matches scope\n- `lobbyFilledAdapter` — checks if player is creator (isCreator === true) and game matches scope\n- `getAdapter(action)` — registry lookup that returns the adapter function or a no-op for unknown actions\n\n**Pattern:**\n1. Pure functions with no side effects\n2. Helper constants: `NO_PROGRESS` and `ONE_PROGRESS` for consistent returns\n3. Helper function `matchesScope()` for scope filtering logic\n4. All adapters follow the same signature and return structure\n5. Registry as a Map, with `getAdapter()` as the public lookup interface\n6. Each adapter checks scope first (returns NO_PROGRESS if scope doesn't match), then checks specific conditions\n\nThis is clean and extensible—new adapters just need to follow the `VerificationAdapter` type and be added to the registry."}],"totalDurationMs":8685,"totalTokens":32563,"totalToolUseCount":1,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5311,"cache_read_input_tokens":26755,"output_tokens":492,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5311},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MCLcKnKnbWyDKqts3jasKY","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t/**\n2\t * Event producer — inserts an event into the queue within an existing\n3\t * database transaction so the event is committed atomically with the\n4\t * triggering operation.\n5\t */\n6\t\n7\timport type postgres from \"postgres\";\n8\timport type { EventType } from \"./event-types.js\";\n9\t\n10\t/** The transaction/sql handle accepted by emitEvent — works with both sql and tx from sql.begin(). */\n11\texport type SqlOrTransaction = postgres.Sql;\n12\t\n13\texport interface EmitEventOptions {\n14\t  maxAttempts?: number; // default: 3\n15\t  scheduledAt?: Date; // default: now\n16\t}\n17\t\n18\texport async function emitEvent(\n19\t  tx: SqlOrTransaction,\n20\t  eventType: EventType,\n21\t  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n22\t  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n23\t): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }> {\n24\t  const maxAttempts = options?.maxAttempts ?? 3;\n25\t  const scheduledAt = options?.scheduledAt ?? new Date();\n26\t\n27\t  const rows = await tx<{ id: string }[]>`\n28\t    INSERT INTO event_queue (event_type, payload, max_attempts, scheduled_at)\n29\t    VALUES (${eventType}, ${tx.json(payload as postgres.JSONValue)}, ${maxAttempts}, ${scheduledAt})\n30\t    RETURNING id\n31\t  `;\n32\t\n33\t  return { eventId: BigInt(rows[0]!.id) };\n34\t}\n35\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018VhPYzbAyLvaxkyKr8pAVh","session_id":"704bd991-5045-4113-8fa3-9bd3dc1e7fdb","uuid":"fcda07d2-3b83-46f5-a11a-dd11b57ac6dc","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:38:07.034Z"}
