{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018VhPYzbAyLvaxkyKr8pAVh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary report:\n\n## Event Queue Handler Patterns - Comprehensive Report\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the backend codebase, here's the complete documentation of the event queue handler patterns:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Handler Registry Pattern**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts` (Lines 1-31)\n\nThe registry uses a simple Map-based pattern with typed registration:\n\n```typescript\nexport type EventHandler = (\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n) => Promise<void>;\n\nexport function registerHandler(\n  eventType: EventType,\n  handler: EventHandler,\n): void {\n  handlers.set(eventType, handler);\n}\n\nexport function getHandler(eventType: string): EventHandler | undefined {\n  return handlers.get(eventType);\n}\n\nexport function clearHandlers(): void {\n  handlers.clear();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- One handler per event type (no pub/sub fan-out in v1)\n- Handlers must be idempotent - re-processing is a safe no-op\n- Registry is a Map<string, EventHandler>\n- Clearance function available for test isolation\n\n---\n\n### 2. **EventHandler Function Signature**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts` (Lines 10-12)\n\n```typescript\nexport type EventHandler = (\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n) => Promise<void>;\n```\n\n**Contract:** \n- Takes a single parameter: `payload` (Record<string, unknown>)\n- Returns a Promise<void>\n- Must not throw if retryable; throw only for retriable errors\n- Idempotency is required since handlers may execute multiple times\n\n---\n\n### 3. **emitEvent Function Signature**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport type SqlOrTransaction = postgres.Sql;\n\nexport interface EmitEventOptions {\n  maxAttempts?: number; // default: 3\n  scheduledAt?: Date; // default: now\n}\n\nexport async function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }> {\n  const maxAttempts = options?.maxAttempts ?? 3;\n  const scheduledAt = options?.scheduledAt ?? new Date();\n\n  const rows = await tx<{ id: string }[]>`\n    INSERT INTO event_queue (event_type, payload, max_attempts, scheduled_at)\n    VALUES (${eventType}, ${tx.json(payload as postgres.JSONValue)}, ${maxAttempts}, ${scheduledAt})\n    RETURNING id\n  `;\n\n  return { eventId: BigInt(rows[0]!.id) };\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **tx parameter:** Works with both `sql` and `tx` from `sql.begin()` (transaction handles)\n- **eventType:** Must be from EventTypes enum\n- **payload:** JSON-serializable Record<string, unknown>\n- **Options:** Optional maxAttempts (default 3) and scheduledAt (default now)\n- **Return:** Object with eventId as BigInt\n- **Atomicity:** Committed together with the triggering operation within the same transaction\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Db Interface - Key Properties for Events**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` (Lines 669-681)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  // ... many methods ...\n\n  /**\n   * Execute a function within a database transaction.\n   * All db methods called on the transactional Db share the same transaction.\n   * Rolls back on error, commits on success.\n   */\n  withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>;\n\n  /** Expose the underlying SQL/transaction handle for use with emitEvent(). */\n  // eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any\n  readonly rawSql: any;\n\n  /** Gracefully close the connection pool. */\n  close(): Promise<void>;\n}\n```\n\n**withTransaction Pattern:**\n```typescript\nasync withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T> {\n  // eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any\n  return sql.begin(async (txSql: any) => fn(createDb(databaseUrl, txSql)));\n}\n```\n\n**Usage:**\n- `withTransaction()` allows wrapping operations in a database transaction\n- All db methods on the transactional Db share the same transaction\n- Rolls back on error, commits on success\n- The `rawSql` property exposes the underlying postgres.Sql handle for use with `emitEvent()`\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Event Types**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n} as const;\n\nexport type EventType = (typeof EventTypes)[keyof typeof EventTypes];\n```\n\n**Pattern:** String literal types derived from const object for compile-time type safety.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Existing Handler Examples**\n\n#### **A. Referral Claim Handler (Factory Pattern)**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts` (Lines 1-183)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface ClaimHandlerDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n}\n\nexport function createClaimHandler(deps: ClaimHandlerDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair } = deps;\n\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    const claimId = payload.claimId as string;\n    const userId = payload.userId as string;\n    const wallet = payload.wallet as string;\n    const amountLamports = payload.amountLamports as string;\n\n    if (!claimId || !userId || !wallet || !amountLamports) {\n      throw new Error(\n        `referral.claim_requested: malformed payload — missing claimId, userId, wallet, or amountLamports`,\n      );\n    }\n\n    // 1. Load claim and check idempotency\n    const claim = await db.getReferralClaim(claimId);\n    if (!claim) {\n      logger.warn(\"referral claim handler: claim not found\", { claimId });\n      return; // no-op — event may reference a deleted/invalid claim\n    }\n\n    if (claim.status === \"completed\") {\n      logger.info(\"referral claim handler: already completed, skipping\", { claimId });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (claim.status === \"failed\") {\n      logger.info(\"referral claim handler: permanently failed, skipping\", { claimId });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // 2. Update status to processing (from pending or error)\n    await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, \"processing\");\n\n    try {\n      // 3. Re-verify available balance >= claim amount\n      const pendingStr = await db.getPendingBalanceByUserId(userId);\n      const pending = BigInt(pendingStr);\n      const amount = BigInt(amountLamports);\n\n      if (pending < amount) {\n        // Insufficient balance is a permanent failure\n        await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, \"failed\", {\n          error: `Insufficient balance: pending=${pendingStr}, claim=${amountLamports}`,\n        });\n        logger.warn(\"referral claim handler: insufficient balance\", {\n          claimId, userId, wallet, pending: pendingStr, amount: amountLamports,\n        });\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // 4. Execute SOL transfer from server keypair to player wallet\n      const recipient = new PublicKey(wallet);\n      const lamports = Number(amount);\n\n      const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n        await connection.getLatestBlockhash(\"confirmed\");\n\n      const tx = new Transaction({\n        feePayer: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n        blockhash,\n        lastValidBlockHeight,\n      });\n\n      tx.add(\n        SystemProgram.transfer({\n          fromPubkey: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n          toPubkey: recipient,\n          lamports,\n        }),\n      );\n\n      tx.sign(serverKeypair);\n\n      const txSignature = await connection.sendRawTransaction(tx.serialize(), {\n        skipPreflight: false,\n      });\n\n      // Wait for confirmation\n      const confirmation = await connection.confirmTransaction(\n        { signature: txSignature, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight },\n        \"confirmed\",\n      );\n\n      if (confirmation.value.err) {\n        throw new Error(\n          `Transaction confirmed with error: ${JSON.stringify(confirmation.value.err)}`,\n        );\n      }\n\n      // 5. Record success\n      await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, \"completed\", { txSignature });\n      logger.info(\"referral claim handler: transfer completed\", {\n        claimId, userId, wallet, amountLamports, txSignature,\n      });\n    } catch (err) {\n      // 6. Transient failure — increment retry count\n      const errorMsg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : \"Unknown transfer error\";\n      const nextRetry = claim.retry_count + 1;\n      const isFinal = nextRetry >= MAX_CLAIM_RETRIES;\n      const nextStatus = isFinal ? \"failed\" : \"error\";\n\n      await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, nextStatus, {\n        error: errorMsg,\n        incrementRetry: true,\n      });\n\n      if (isFinal) {\n        logger.error(\n          \"referral claim handler: max retries exceeded, permanently failed\",\n          { claimId, userId, wallet, amountLamports, retries: nextRetry, error: errorMsg },\n        );\n        return; // Don't rethrow — claim is permanently dead\n      }\n\n      logger.warn(\n        \"referral claim handler: transient error, will retry\",\n        { claimId, userId, wallet, amountLamports, retry: nextRetry, error: errorMsg },\n      );\n      // Re-throw so the queue worker retries with exponential backoff\n      throw err;\n    }\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern notes:**\n- Factory function receives dependencies injection (Db, Connection, Keypair)\n- Returns an EventHandler function\n- Validates payload at entry\n- Implements idempotency checks (skip if already completed/failed)\n- On transient errors: rethrow to trigger queue retry with exponential backoff\n- On permanent errors: mark as failed and don't rethrow\n\n#### **B. Challenge Adapters (Verification Registry Pattern)**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/challenge-adapters.ts` (Lines 1-152)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface GameSettledPlayer {\n  userId: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  amountLamports: string;\n  isWinner: boolean | null; // null = refund\n  payoutLamports: string;\n  isCreator: boolean;\n}\n\nexport interface GameSettledPayload {\n  roundId: string;\n  roundPda: string;\n  game: \"coinflip\" | \"lord\" | \"closecall\";\n  players: GameSettledPlayer[];\n  feeLamports: string;\n  settledAt: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ChallengeAssignment {\n  id: number;\n  challengeId: number;\n  action: string;\n  scope: string; // 'any' | 'coinflip' | 'lord' | 'closecall'\n  condition: string;\n  target: number;\n  progress: number;\n  status: string;\n}\n\nexport interface AdapterResult {\n  shouldProgress: boolean;\n  progressDelta: number;\n}\n\nexport type VerificationAdapter = (\n  event: GameSettledPayload,\n  player: GameSettledPlayer,\n  assignment: ChallengeAssignment,\n) => AdapterResult;\n\n// Quest eligibility check\nexport function questEligible(player: GameSettledPlayer): boolean {\n  return player.isWinner !== null; // Exclude refunds\n}\n\n// Adapter implementations\nfunction gameCompletedAdapter(\n  event: GameSettledPayload,\n  _player: GameSettledPlayer,\n  assignment: ChallengeAssignment,\n): AdapterResult {\n  if (!matchesScope(event.game, assignment.scope)) return NO_PROGRESS;\n  return ONE_PROGRESS;\n}\n\nfunction gameWonAdapter(\n  event: GameSettledPayload,\n  player: GameSettledPlayer,\n  assignment: ChallengeAssignment,\n): AdapterResult {\n  if (!matchesScope(event.game, assignment.scope)) return NO_PROGRESS;\n  if (player.isWinner !== true) return NO_PROGRESS;\n  return ONE_PROGRESS;\n}\n\nfunction lobbyFilledAdapter(\n  event: GameSettledPayload,\n  player: GameSettledPlayer,\n  assignment: ChallengeAssignment,\n): AdapterResult {\n  if (!matchesScope(event.game, assignment.scope)) return NO_PROGRESS;\n  if (!player.isCreator) return NO_PROGRESS;\n  return ONE_PROGRESS;\n}\n\n// Adapter registry\nconst adapterRegistry = new Map<string, VerificationAdapter>([\n  [\"game_completed\", gameCompletedAdapter],\n  [\"game_won\", gameWonAdapter],\n  [\"lobby_filled\", lobbyFilledAdapter],\n]);\n\nexport function getAdapter(action: string): VerificationAdapter {\n  const adapter = adapterRegistry.get(action);\n  if (!adapter) {\n    logger.warn(\"Unknown challenge adapter action type\", { action });\n    return () => NO_PROGRESS;\n  }\n  return adapter;\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern notes:**\n- Pure functions with no side effects\n- Adapters evaluate event against challenge assignment\n- Registry pattern for pluggable verification logic\n- Unknown actions log warning and return safe default\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Event Queue Worker**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport interface EventWorkerOptions {\n  pollIntervalMs?: number; // default: 1500\n  batchSize?: number; // default: 10\n}\n\nexport function createEventWorker(\n  sql: postgres.Sql,\n  options?: EventWorkerOptions,\n): EventWorker {\n  // Polls event_queue table\n  async function poll(): Promise<void> {\n    // Claim a batch of pending events atomically\n    const events = await sql<EventRow[]>`\n      UPDATE event_queue\n      SET status = 'processing', started_at = now()\n      WHERE id IN (\n        SELECT id FROM event_queue\n        WHERE status = 'pending' AND scheduled_at <= now()\n        ORDER BY scheduled_at\n        LIMIT ${batchSize}\n        FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED\n      )\n      RETURNING *\n    `;\n\n    for (const event of events) {\n      const handler = getHandler(event.event_type);\n\n      if (!handler) {\n        // No handler registered — mark dead immediately\n        await sql`\n          UPDATE event_queue\n          SET status = 'dead',\n              error = ${\"no handler registered for: \" + event.event_type},\n              completed_at = now()\n          WHERE id = ${event.id}\n        `;\n        logger.warn(\"MANUAL REVIEW NEEDED: unhandled event type\", {\n          eventId: event.id,\n          eventType: event.event_type,\n          transition: \"processing → dead\",\n        });\n        continue;\n      }\n\n      try {\n        await handler(event.payload);\n\n        // Success — mark completed\n        await sql`\n          UPDATE event_queue\n          SET status = 'completed', completed_at = now()\n          WHERE id = ${event.id}\n        `;\n      } catch (err) {\n        // Failure handling — increment attempts and decide retry vs dead\n        const attempts = event.attempts + 1;\n        const errorMessage = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n\n        if (attempts >= event.max_attempts) {\n          // Exceeded max attempts — mark dead\n          await sql`\n            UPDATE event_queue\n            SET status = 'dead',\n                attempts = ${attempts},\n                error = ${errorMessage},\n                completed_at = now()\n            WHERE id = ${event.id}\n          `;\n        } else {\n          // Retry with exponential backoff\n          const backoffSeconds = getBackoffSeconds(attempts);\n          await sql`\n            UPDATE event_queue\n            SET status = 'pending',\n                attempts = ${attempts},\n                error = ${errorMessage},\n                scheduled_at = now() + ${backoffSeconds + \" seconds\"}::interval\n            WHERE id = ${event.id}\n          `;\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  \n  // ... setTimeout(loop, interval) pattern\n}\n\nexport function getBackoffSeconds(attempt: number): number {\n  switch (attempt) {\n    case 1:\n      return 5;\n    case 2:\n      return 30;\n    default:\n      return 300;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Polls event_queue table on interval (default 1500ms)\n- FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED for safe concurrent processing\n- Batches events (default 10 per poll)\n- Exponential backoff: 5s → 30s → 300s\n- Status transitions: pending → processing → (completed/dead) or pending (retry)\n- Dead events: require manual review\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Handler Registration in Main App**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { createEventWorker, registerHandler, EventTypes } from \"./queue/index.js\";\nimport { createClaimHandler } from \"./queue/handlers/referral-claim.js\";\n\n// Register handler with dependencies\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n\n// Start event queue worker\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Integration Test Example**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts` (Lines 70-100)\n\n```typescript\nit(\"happy path: handler called and event status = completed\", async () => {\n  let handlerCalled = false;\n  let capturedPayload: Record<string, unknown> | null = null;\n\n  registerHandler(EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED, async (payload) => {\n    handlerCalled = true;\n    capturedPayload = payload;\n  });\n\n  const payload = { referrerWallet: \"abc\", roundId: \"test-round\" };\n  \n  // Emit event within transaction\n  await sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n    await emitEvent(\n      tx as unknown as postgres.Sql,\n      EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED,\n      payload,\n    );\n  });\n\n  // Start worker and wait for handler\n  const worker = createEventWorker(sql, { pollIntervalMs: 100 });\n  worker.start();\n\n  await waitFor(() => handlerCalled, 3000);\n  worker.stop();\n\n  expect(handlerCalled).toBe(true);\n  expect(capturedPayload).toEqual(payload);\n\n  // Verify DB status\n  const rows = await sql`SELECT * FROM event_queue WHERE status = 'completed'`;\n  expect(rows).toHaveLength(1);\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe event queue handler pattern follows these key principles:\n\n1. **Registry Pattern:** Simple Map-based handler lookup by event type\n2. **Dependency Injection:** Handlers are factory functions receiving required dependencies\n3. **Idempotency:** Handlers must be safe to re-execute (check existing state first)\n4. **Atomic Emission:** Events emitted within transactions via `emitEvent(tx, ...)`\n5. **Exponential Backoff Retry:** Failed events retry with 5s → 30s → 300s intervals\n6. **Dead Letter Queue:** Events exhausting retries marked as 'dead' for manual review\n7. **Concurrent Safety:** FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED prevents duplicate processing\n8. **Error Distinction:** Permanent errors don't rethrow (mark failed); retriable errors rethrow\n\nAll paths and line numbers are absolute file paths in the `/workspaces/rng-utopia` directory."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"704bd991-5045-4113-8fa3-9bd3dc1e7fdb","uuid":"f217567a-ac1f-46dc-80a3-c32ff99ed3a4","timestamp":"2026-04-03T19:39:04.087Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the event queue handler patterns in this backend codebase. Specifically:\n\n1. How existing event handlers are structured and registered in `backend/services/backend/src/queue/`\n2. The handler registry pattern - how handlers get mapped to event types\n3. The `emitEvent` function signature\n4. The `Db` interface in `backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` - especially the `rawSql` property and `withTransaction` pattern\n5. The existing event-types in `backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n6. Any existing handler file as a reference pattern (e.g., how a handler function is exported, params it takes)\n\nFocus on finding the handler registry, handler file examples, and the Db interface. Report file paths, line numbers, and relevant code snippets. Be thorough.","agentId":"a0df026653f7d7c28","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed summary report:\n\n## Event Queue Handler Patterns - Comprehensive Report\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the backend codebase, here's the complete documentation of the event queue handler patterns:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Handler Registry Pattern**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts` (Lines 1-31)\n\nThe registry uses a simple Map-based pattern with typed registration:\n\n```typescript\nexport type EventHandler = (\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n) => Promise<void>;\n\nexport function registerHandler(\n  eventType: EventType,\n  handler: EventHandler,\n): void {\n  handlers.set(eventType, handler);\n}\n\nexport function getHandler(eventType: string): EventHandler | undefined {\n  return handlers.get(eventType);\n}\n\nexport function clearHandlers(): void {\n  handlers.clear();\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- One handler per event type (no pub/sub fan-out in v1)\n- Handlers must be idempotent - re-processing is a safe no-op\n- Registry is a Map<string, EventHandler>\n- Clearance function available for test isolation\n\n---\n\n### 2. **EventHandler Function Signature**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handler-registry.ts` (Lines 10-12)\n\n```typescript\nexport type EventHandler = (\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n) => Promise<void>;\n```\n\n**Contract:** \n- Takes a single parameter: `payload` (Record<string, unknown>)\n- Returns a Promise<void>\n- Must not throw if retryable; throw only for retriable errors\n- Idempotency is required since handlers may execute multiple times\n\n---\n\n### 3. **emitEvent Function Signature**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/emit-event.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport type SqlOrTransaction = postgres.Sql;\n\nexport interface EmitEventOptions {\n  maxAttempts?: number; // default: 3\n  scheduledAt?: Date; // default: now\n}\n\nexport async function emitEvent(\n  tx: SqlOrTransaction,\n  eventType: EventType,\n  payload: Record<string, unknown>,\n  options?: EmitEventOptions,\n): Promise<{ eventId: bigint }> {\n  const maxAttempts = options?.maxAttempts ?? 3;\n  const scheduledAt = options?.scheduledAt ?? new Date();\n\n  const rows = await tx<{ id: string }[]>`\n    INSERT INTO event_queue (event_type, payload, max_attempts, scheduled_at)\n    VALUES (${eventType}, ${tx.json(payload as postgres.JSONValue)}, ${maxAttempts}, ${scheduledAt})\n    RETURNING id\n  `;\n\n  return { eventId: BigInt(rows[0]!.id) };\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **tx parameter:** Works with both `sql` and `tx` from `sql.begin()` (transaction handles)\n- **eventType:** Must be from EventTypes enum\n- **payload:** JSON-serializable Record<string, unknown>\n- **Options:** Optional maxAttempts (default 3) and scheduledAt (default now)\n- **Return:** Object with eventId as BigInt\n- **Atomicity:** Committed together with the triggering operation within the same transaction\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Db Interface - Key Properties for Events**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` (Lines 669-681)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  // ... many methods ...\n\n  /**\n   * Execute a function within a database transaction.\n   * All db methods called on the transactional Db share the same transaction.\n   * Rolls back on error, commits on success.\n   */\n  withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>;\n\n  /** Expose the underlying SQL/transaction handle for use with emitEvent(). */\n  // eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any\n  readonly rawSql: any;\n\n  /** Gracefully close the connection pool. */\n  close(): Promise<void>;\n}\n```\n\n**withTransaction Pattern:**\n```typescript\nasync withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T> {\n  // eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any\n  return sql.begin(async (txSql: any) => fn(createDb(databaseUrl, txSql)));\n}\n```\n\n**Usage:**\n- `withTransaction()` allows wrapping operations in a database transaction\n- All db methods on the transactional Db share the same transaction\n- Rolls back on error, commits on success\n- The `rawSql` property exposes the underlying postgres.Sql handle for use with `emitEvent()`\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Event Types**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/event-types.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport const EventTypes = {\n  REFERRAL_CODE_APPLIED: \"referral.code_applied\",\n  REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED: \"referral.game_settled\",\n  REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED: \"referral.claim_requested\",\n  GAME_SETTLED: \"game.settled\",\n  REWARD_POOL_FUND: \"reward.pool_fund\",\n  POINTS_GRANT: \"points.grant\",\n  CRATE_DROP: \"crate.drop\",\n  CRATE_SOL_PAYOUT: \"crate.sol_payout\",\n} as const;\n\nexport type EventType = (typeof EventTypes)[keyof typeof EventTypes];\n```\n\n**Pattern:** String literal types derived from const object for compile-time type safety.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Existing Handler Examples**\n\n#### **A. Referral Claim Handler (Factory Pattern)**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts` (Lines 1-183)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface ClaimHandlerDeps {\n  db: Db;\n  connection: Connection;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n}\n\nexport function createClaimHandler(deps: ClaimHandlerDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair } = deps;\n\n  return async (payload: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> => {\n    const claimId = payload.claimId as string;\n    const userId = payload.userId as string;\n    const wallet = payload.wallet as string;\n    const amountLamports = payload.amountLamports as string;\n\n    if (!claimId || !userId || !wallet || !amountLamports) {\n      throw new Error(\n        `referral.claim_requested: malformed payload — missing claimId, userId, wallet, or amountLamports`,\n      );\n    }\n\n    // 1. Load claim and check idempotency\n    const claim = await db.getReferralClaim(claimId);\n    if (!claim) {\n      logger.warn(\"referral claim handler: claim not found\", { claimId });\n      return; // no-op — event may reference a deleted/invalid claim\n    }\n\n    if (claim.status === \"completed\") {\n      logger.info(\"referral claim handler: already completed, skipping\", { claimId });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (claim.status === \"failed\") {\n      logger.info(\"referral claim handler: permanently failed, skipping\", { claimId });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // 2. Update status to processing (from pending or error)\n    await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, \"processing\");\n\n    try {\n      // 3. Re-verify available balance >= claim amount\n      const pendingStr = await db.getPendingBalanceByUserId(userId);\n      const pending = BigInt(pendingStr);\n      const amount = BigInt(amountLamports);\n\n      if (pending < amount) {\n        // Insufficient balance is a permanent failure\n        await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, \"failed\", {\n          error: `Insufficient balance: pending=${pendingStr}, claim=${amountLamports}`,\n        });\n        logger.warn(\"referral claim handler: insufficient balance\", {\n          claimId, userId, wallet, pending: pendingStr, amount: amountLamports,\n        });\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // 4. Execute SOL transfer from server keypair to player wallet\n      const recipient = new PublicKey(wallet);\n      const lamports = Number(amount);\n\n      const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n        await connection.getLatestBlockhash(\"confirmed\");\n\n      const tx = new Transaction({\n        feePayer: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n        blockhash,\n        lastValidBlockHeight,\n      });\n\n      tx.add(\n        SystemProgram.transfer({\n          fromPubkey: serverKeypair.publicKey,\n          toPubkey: recipient,\n          lamports,\n        }),\n      );\n\n      tx.sign(serverKeypair);\n\n      const txSignature = await connection.sendRawTransaction(tx.serialize(), {\n        skipPreflight: false,\n      });\n\n      // Wait for confirmation\n      const confirmation = await connection.confirmTransaction(\n        { signature: txSignature, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight },\n        \"confirmed\",\n      );\n\n      if (confirmation.value.err) {\n        throw new Error(\n          `Transaction confirmed with error: ${JSON.stringify(confirmation.value.err)}`,\n        );\n      }\n\n      // 5. Record success\n      await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, \"completed\", { txSignature });\n      logger.info(\"referral claim handler: transfer completed\", {\n        claimId, userId, wallet, amountLamports, txSignature,\n      });\n    } catch (err) {\n      // 6. Transient failure — increment retry count\n      const errorMsg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : \"Unknown transfer error\";\n      const nextRetry = claim.retry_count + 1;\n      const isFinal = nextRetry >= MAX_CLAIM_RETRIES;\n      const nextStatus = isFinal ? \"failed\" : \"error\";\n\n      await db.updateClaimStatus(claimId, nextStatus, {\n        error: errorMsg,\n        incrementRetry: true,\n      });\n\n      if (isFinal) {\n        logger.error(\n          \"referral claim handler: max retries exceeded, permanently failed\",\n          { claimId, userId, wallet, amountLamports, retries: nextRetry, error: errorMsg },\n        );\n        return; // Don't rethrow — claim is permanently dead\n      }\n\n      logger.warn(\n        \"referral claim handler: transient error, will retry\",\n        { claimId, userId, wallet, amountLamports, retry: nextRetry, error: errorMsg },\n      );\n      // Re-throw so the queue worker retries with exponential backoff\n      throw err;\n    }\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern notes:**\n- Factory function receives dependencies injection (Db, Connection, Keypair)\n- Returns an EventHandler function\n- Validates payload at entry\n- Implements idempotency checks (skip if already completed/failed)\n- On transient errors: rethrow to trigger queue retry with exponential backoff\n- On permanent errors: mark as failed and don't rethrow\n\n#### **B. Challenge Adapters (Verification Registry Pattern)**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/handlers/challenge-adapters.ts` (Lines 1-152)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface GameSettledPlayer {\n  userId: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  amountLamports: string;\n  isWinner: boolean | null; // null = refund\n  payoutLamports: string;\n  isCreator: boolean;\n}\n\nexport interface GameSettledPayload {\n  roundId: string;\n  roundPda: string;\n  game: \"coinflip\" | \"lord\" | \"closecall\";\n  players: GameSettledPlayer[];\n  feeLamports: string;\n  settledAt: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ChallengeAssignment {\n  id: number;\n  challengeId: number;\n  action: string;\n  scope: string; // 'any' | 'coinflip' | 'lord' | 'closecall'\n  condition: string;\n  target: number;\n  progress: number;\n  status: string;\n}\n\nexport interface AdapterResult {\n  shouldProgress: boolean;\n  progressDelta: number;\n}\n\nexport type VerificationAdapter = (\n  event: GameSettledPayload,\n  player: GameSettledPlayer,\n  assignment: ChallengeAssignment,\n) => AdapterResult;\n\n// Quest eligibility check\nexport function questEligible(player: GameSettledPlayer): boolean {\n  return player.isWinner !== null; // Exclude refunds\n}\n\n// Adapter implementations\nfunction gameCompletedAdapter(\n  event: GameSettledPayload,\n  _player: GameSettledPlayer,\n  assignment: ChallengeAssignment,\n): AdapterResult {\n  if (!matchesScope(event.game, assignment.scope)) return NO_PROGRESS;\n  return ONE_PROGRESS;\n}\n\nfunction gameWonAdapter(\n  event: GameSettledPayload,\n  player: GameSettledPlayer,\n  assignment: ChallengeAssignment,\n): AdapterResult {\n  if (!matchesScope(event.game, assignment.scope)) return NO_PROGRESS;\n  if (player.isWinner !== true) return NO_PROGRESS;\n  return ONE_PROGRESS;\n}\n\nfunction lobbyFilledAdapter(\n  event: GameSettledPayload,\n  player: GameSettledPlayer,\n  assignment: ChallengeAssignment,\n): AdapterResult {\n  if (!matchesScope(event.game, assignment.scope)) return NO_PROGRESS;\n  if (!player.isCreator) return NO_PROGRESS;\n  return ONE_PROGRESS;\n}\n\n// Adapter registry\nconst adapterRegistry = new Map<string, VerificationAdapter>([\n  [\"game_completed\", gameCompletedAdapter],\n  [\"game_won\", gameWonAdapter],\n  [\"lobby_filled\", lobbyFilledAdapter],\n]);\n\nexport function getAdapter(action: string): VerificationAdapter {\n  const adapter = adapterRegistry.get(action);\n  if (!adapter) {\n    logger.warn(\"Unknown challenge adapter action type\", { action });\n    return () => NO_PROGRESS;\n  }\n  return adapter;\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern notes:**\n- Pure functions with no side effects\n- Adapters evaluate event against challenge assignment\n- Registry pattern for pluggable verification logic\n- Unknown actions log warning and return safe default\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Event Queue Worker**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/worker.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport interface EventWorkerOptions {\n  pollIntervalMs?: number; // default: 1500\n  batchSize?: number; // default: 10\n}\n\nexport function createEventWorker(\n  sql: postgres.Sql,\n  options?: EventWorkerOptions,\n): EventWorker {\n  // Polls event_queue table\n  async function poll(): Promise<void> {\n    // Claim a batch of pending events atomically\n    const events = await sql<EventRow[]>`\n      UPDATE event_queue\n      SET status = 'processing', started_at = now()\n      WHERE id IN (\n        SELECT id FROM event_queue\n        WHERE status = 'pending' AND scheduled_at <= now()\n        ORDER BY scheduled_at\n        LIMIT ${batchSize}\n        FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED\n      )\n      RETURNING *\n    `;\n\n    for (const event of events) {\n      const handler = getHandler(event.event_type);\n\n      if (!handler) {\n        // No handler registered — mark dead immediately\n        await sql`\n          UPDATE event_queue\n          SET status = 'dead',\n              error = ${\"no handler registered for: \" + event.event_type},\n              completed_at = now()\n          WHERE id = ${event.id}\n        `;\n        logger.warn(\"MANUAL REVIEW NEEDED: unhandled event type\", {\n          eventId: event.id,\n          eventType: event.event_type,\n          transition: \"processing → dead\",\n        });\n        continue;\n      }\n\n      try {\n        await handler(event.payload);\n\n        // Success — mark completed\n        await sql`\n          UPDATE event_queue\n          SET status = 'completed', completed_at = now()\n          WHERE id = ${event.id}\n        `;\n      } catch (err) {\n        // Failure handling — increment attempts and decide retry vs dead\n        const attempts = event.attempts + 1;\n        const errorMessage = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n\n        if (attempts >= event.max_attempts) {\n          // Exceeded max attempts — mark dead\n          await sql`\n            UPDATE event_queue\n            SET status = 'dead',\n                attempts = ${attempts},\n                error = ${errorMessage},\n                completed_at = now()\n            WHERE id = ${event.id}\n          `;\n        } else {\n          // Retry with exponential backoff\n          const backoffSeconds = getBackoffSeconds(attempts);\n          await sql`\n            UPDATE event_queue\n            SET status = 'pending',\n                attempts = ${attempts},\n                error = ${errorMessage},\n                scheduled_at = now() + ${backoffSeconds + \" seconds\"}::interval\n            WHERE id = ${event.id}\n          `;\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  \n  // ... setTimeout(loop, interval) pattern\n}\n\nexport function getBackoffSeconds(attempt: number): number {\n  switch (attempt) {\n    case 1:\n      return 5;\n    case 2:\n      return 30;\n    default:\n      return 300;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Polls event_queue table on interval (default 1500ms)\n- FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED for safe concurrent processing\n- Batches events (default 10 per poll)\n- Exponential backoff: 5s → 30s → 300s\n- Status transitions: pending → processing → (completed/dead) or pending (retry)\n- Dead events: require manual review\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Handler Registration in Main App**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { createEventWorker, registerHandler, EventTypes } from \"./queue/index.js\";\nimport { createClaimHandler } from \"./queue/handlers/referral-claim.js\";\n\n// Register handler with dependencies\nregisterHandler(\n  EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED,\n  createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair }),\n);\n\n// Start event queue worker\nconst eventWorker = createEventWorker(sql, {\n  pollIntervalMs: config.eventQueuePollMs,\n});\neventWorker.start();\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Integration Test Example**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/queue/__tests__/queue-integration.test.ts` (Lines 70-100)\n\n```typescript\nit(\"happy path: handler called and event status = completed\", async () => {\n  let handlerCalled = false;\n  let capturedPayload: Record<string, unknown> | null = null;\n\n  registerHandler(EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED, async (payload) => {\n    handlerCalled = true;\n    capturedPayload = payload;\n  });\n\n  const payload = { referrerWallet: \"abc\", roundId: \"test-round\" };\n  \n  // Emit event within transaction\n  await sql.begin(async (tx) => {\n    await emitEvent(\n      tx as unknown as postgres.Sql,\n      EventTypes.REFERRAL_GAME_SETTLED,\n      payload,\n    );\n  });\n\n  // Start worker and wait for handler\n  const worker = createEventWorker(sql, { pollIntervalMs: 100 });\n  worker.start();\n\n  await waitFor(() => handlerCalled, 3000);\n  worker.stop();\n\n  expect(handlerCalled).toBe(true);\n  expect(capturedPayload).toEqual(payload);\n\n  // Verify DB status\n  const rows = await sql`SELECT * FROM event_queue WHERE status = 'completed'`;\n  expect(rows).toHaveLength(1);\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe event queue handler pattern follows these key principles:\n\n1. **Registry Pattern:** Simple Map-based handler lookup by event type\n2. **Dependency Injection:** Handlers are factory functions receiving required dependencies\n3. **Idempotency:** Handlers must be safe to re-execute (check existing state first)\n4. **Atomic Emission:** Events emitted within transactions via `emitEvent(tx, ...)`\n5. **Exponential Backoff Retry:** Failed events retry with 5s → 30s → 300s intervals\n6. **Dead Letter Queue:** Events exhausting retries marked as 'dead' for manual review\n7. **Concurrent Safety:** FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED prevents duplicate processing\n8. **Error Distinction:** Permanent errors don't rethrow (mark failed); retriable errors rethrow\n\nAll paths and line numbers are absolute file paths in the `/workspaces/rng-utopia` directory."}],"totalDurationMs":72395,"totalTokens":55417,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1178,"cache_read_input_tokens":48905,"output_tokens":5329,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1178},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
